reviewText: I bought the 8 Films to Die for After Dark Horrorfest 2 disc set at my local Walmart for only $5.00, which isn't bad for 8 movies.The movies are:Disc 1:Autopsy (unrated; 2008)Slaughter (Rated R; 2008)The Broken (Rated R; 2008)The Butterfly Effect 3: Revelations (Rated R; 2008)Disc 2:Perkins' 14 (Rated R; 2009)Voices (Rated R; 2008)Dying Breed (Rated R; 2008)From Within (Rated R; 2007)
summary: 8 Horror Movies for at a Great Price!
Title: 8 FILMS to DIE For AFTER DARK Horrorfest III (includes Autopsy (2009) The Broken (2008) Slaughter (2009) Perkins'14 (2009) Dying Breed (2008) From Within (2008) Voices (2007) The Butterfly Effect 3:Revelations (2009)

reviewText: If your trying to collect all the movies this is your best bet. And the cheapest. The movies are alright at best most are on the b movie side but there still enjoyable.
Title: 8 FILMS to DIE For AFTER DARK Horrorfest III (includes Autopsy (2009) The Broken (2008) Slaughter (2009) Perkins'14 (2009) Dying Breed (2008) From Within (2008) Voices (2007) The Butterfly Effect 3:Revelations (2009)

reviewText: when i first heard of after dark horror fest back in 06 the previews and the hype had me expecting some of the scariest flicks ever made...but...no lol ive come to expect b movie material with decent films or horrible ones. this 8 pack wasnt too bad. i must say i was able to enjoy all of them. are they scary, of course not although there were a few creepy moments. but for 5 bucks and 8 movies im satisfied. out of all eight i have to say The Broken was my personal favorite but they were all decent.

reviewText: Just picked this up at Walmart for $5.00.  I have the original box set(each movie on a single disc) that cost me around $60.00.  Since I haven't opened the box set yet I will probably watch them on this 2 disc version first...but just wondering if the video quality will be that different between the 2????
